@NODE HISTORY "7. Program history & future"
@PREV BUGS
@NEXT LEGAL

@{B}@{U}Program history@{UU}@{UB}

 (The a, b, c etc. versions were not released, beta (ß) and  gamma  (y)  versions
 only given to testers.)

 Upper case letters signify major or important changes, lower case minor ones:

 N: New feature added
 E: Enhanced old feature
 I: Internal change
 U: Change of usage
 B: Bugfix

 History of versions 1.0 to 3.0 is short cut.

 1.0  (24.02.94)  N: Initial Release
 2.0  (23.05.94)  N: Added GUI
 3.0  (29.01.95)  E: Overhauled two column front end
                  N: Menu for settings added
 3.1a (04.02.95)  n: Two new options for join words (left/right aligned)
                  e: Two new Arexx commands (GETSTYLE/SETSTYLE)
                  e: Arexx commands GET/SETMODE now work for checkbox only gadgets
                  N: Title mode added
 3.1b (17.03.95)  b: Used to crash when window couldn't be opened - fixed
                  N: Translated to Italian by Emanuele Bolognesi (many thanks!)
 3.1c (20.04.95)  E: Screen shot for every option with values
                  b: Ovals drawn from left to right etc. caused problems - fixed
                  b: On-line help now works with amigaguide.library V34+ (OS2.x)
 3.1  (21.05.95)  b: Erasing the text gadget + Ok now correctly shows a requester
                  e: Slightly improved results with titlemode + adjust width
                  e: Updated some parts of the manual
 3.11 (17.10.95)  N: Danish translation by Mads Lie Jensen (thanks a lot!)
                  i: Non-english texts are now in separate files to save memory
                  e: Text block/oval prefs now work when an object is selected
                  e: Help for configuration specific problems in the manual
 3.12a (22.02.96) b: Fixed bug that caused Final Writer not to find the right font
                  b: Other minor bugs fixed
 3.12b (27.07.96) n: Automatic bug-report generation
 3.12c (07.10.96) b: Now properly works with the public screen of Final Writer 5
                  u: "Use F. Writer's screen" not needed anymore with FW5, removed
 3.12d (14.10.96) u: Removed "Window beneath pointer","Delete","Group" options
                  u: Removed "Rotate: Delta","Rotate: Like textblock" options
                  e: Now characters are drawn with the baseline exactly on the oval
 3.12  (31.10.96) e: Manual now contains a description how to create the examples
                  b: Corrected bug in Danish Installer-script
 3.13a (09.02.97) b: No longer adds leading space to default textblock text
                  e: Now takes default text block text if no other text given
                  N: Norwegian translation by Kim Roar Utsi (thanks a lot!)
 3.13  (15.02.97) b: Now uses SoftSans if a font is not installed (used to abort)
                  e: Now asks whether to print bug report after a bug
                  b: Bug report didn't list error message correctly
                  b: Now can be terminated after Final Writer 5 without problems
 3.14a (08.05.97) b: Removed some bugs in the cleanup code
                  b: Should now be correctly localized under OS3.1 as well
 3.14  (19.05.97) b: Removed code that caused rare system crashes (see also @{"here" LINK BUGS 4})
                  b: Other smaller bugs fixed
                  e: Somewhat improved (de)installation-script
                  e: Uses installed language if Locale-language not installed
 3.2a  (30.06.97) b: Now works with FinalWriter 97 and it's frames
                  b: Window opened too small on some systems - workaround added
                  e: Doesn't alter document anymore if no wrapping is done
 3.2b  (07.07.97) b: Didn't load last used text and oval coordinates correctly
                  N: Align option added
 3.2c  (17.07.97) e: If font is too wide/high gadgets are scaled to fit on screen
                  b: Corrected some bugs in bugreport script
                  U: Textblock prefs for text and shadow can be set via a gadget
 3.2d  (07.09.97) U: "Colour" and "Pattern from..." options merged into "Prefs"
                  U: "Shadow" option now separate
                  e: Shadow can now have different font/size etc.
                  u: Text/oval prefs menus not needed anymore - removed
                  n: Quit menu option added
 3.2e  (13.09.97) u: Quit now also saves the settings
                  u: Look of the requester slightly changed
                  e: Font etc. of text now stored when you quit FinalWrapper
 3.2f  (04.10.97) u: Adjust arc for spiral option removed (now always done)
                  e: If prefs are changed, prefs gadget is set to "text prefs"
 3.2g  (14.10.97) e: Aborting now also possible via keyboard
                  e: Zipped window much smaller
                  i: Own directory FinalWrapper: for all files
                  u: Can't be run before Final Writer anymore (who needs that...)
                  e: Tables for character size of a font for faster drawing
 3.2h  (26.10.97) u: Only scans paragraph if no text given (avoids unwanted scans)
                  b: Adjust crashed sometimes with anticlockwise arc - fixed
                  e: Spaces no longer drawn to save time
                  e: Other minor speed improvements
 3.2i  (01.12.97) b: Removed some bugs with Join words
                  b: Now works if FinalWrapper: is defined with Assign DEFER
 3.2j  (14.12.97) b: Several smaller bugs corrected
                  u: Limits for input values better (e.g. >= 5 for arc)
                  b: Help key now works when a gadget is active
 3.2   (28.12.97) e: Repeated installation of same version now possible
                  e: Installer script improved
                  b: Some bugs in the Arexx-port have been removed
                  e: Updated tutorial and other macros
 3.21  (03.01.98) b: Fixed bug in Installer-script
 3.22a (16.01.98) u: No more scans current paragraph on startup if no other text
 3.22b (16.02.98) b: Installer-script no longer overwrites newer library versions
 3.22  (06.07.02) n: Install/deinstall icons added (were missed by some users ;-)
                  u: FinalWrapper is no longer Shareware.
                  n: FontMaps/Tools/ FWKeyFile thus included in regular release
                  n: Source code for SetLanguage and FWKeyFile provided in Source
                  b: For characters to be drawn off-page, coords are changed to 0
                  b: Fixed bug with setting prefs and decimal mode COMMA

 A lot of work has been put into testing the macro and hundreds of bugs have been
 removed.  It  seems  to run pretty reliable now, although there surely are still
 some bugs undiscovered till now.


@{B}@{U}The future of FinalWrapper@{UU}@{UB}
 
 There are currently no plans for any updates.

 You can still write me about bugs and improvement ideas. If you  tell  me  about
 bugs,  I  might  try  to  fix them and send you a version with the bug fixed, if
 possible. I don't make any guarantees about this, however.

 I'll also upload new versions to the AmiNet directory @{B}biz/swood@{UB}.

 See also @{"Bug reports" LINK BUGS 82}.
@ENDNODE
@NODE LEGAL "8. Legal stuff"
@PREV HISTORY
@NEXT THANKS

@{B}@{U}Law and order@{UU}@{UB}

 @{B}* Distribution:@{UB}

 Starting with version 3.22,  FinalWrapper is no longer  shareware as it used  to
 be, but has now  been put in the Public Domain. You may freely  redistribute it,
 use it, improve it etc.

 This change applies backwards to all previous versions. Existing registred users
 are also explicitly allowed to redistribute their personal key files "FWKeyFile"
 as they please. A key file for all users is included with this release.

 If any copyright notice for  FinalWrapper  or  its  documentation  should  still
 appear anywhere in this distribution it is void.

 The reason for this change is that I no longer spend much time programming in my
 spare  time  (software engineering now being my job). Besides that, I didn't get
 too many registration requests lately anyway.

 Many thanks to all registred users for their donations!

 Although you are no longer obliged to register, I still like hearing from you! I
 don't  plan to do updates, but you can still contact me if you discover a bug or
 have  problems with  installation. It might  take  some time until you hear from
 me, however,  depending  on  when I find  time  to  look  at  it. See  also  the
 @{"section about bugs" LINK BUGS}.

 @{B}* Updates:@{UB}

 The newest version should always be available on AmiNet  (@{B}biz/swood@{UB}).

 If you need an update on disk or via e-mail, please contact  me,  preferably  by
 e-mail.

 @{B}* Disclaimer:@{UB}
 
 You use the program at your own risk. Neither I nor  any  other  author  of  any
 included  file can be made responsible for any damage caused by any part of this
 distribution.


 @{B}* Copyrights:@{UB}

 FinalWrapper is in the Public Domain.
 
 Final Writer is (c) by SoftWood Inc.

 The Installer and AmigaGuide are (c) by Amiga International, but they  both  can
 be found on Fish Disk 870.

 Workbench and Amiga are trademarks of Amiga International

 Arexx and rexxsupport.library are (c) by William S. Hawes and Amiga Int.
 
 GoldEd is (c) by Dietmar Eilert

 The icons are (c) by Martin Huttenloher

 reqtools.library is (c) by Nico François and Magnus Holmgren

 rexxreqtools.library is (c) by Rafael D'Halleweyn

 If I should have unintentionally violated a Copyright, please let me know!

@ENDNODE
